<TITLE> Forest ministry donates 1 day's salary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 5 (bdnews24.com)  Forest and environment ministry has come forward to help the victims and affected people from the Nimtali fire, the worst in the country's recent history, which claimed at least 117 lives on Thursday night. The ministry officials will donate their one day's salary in the prime minister's aid fund for this purpose. State minister Hasan Mahmud revealed this on Saturday, on the 'World Environment Day', while visiting the injured at the burns unit of Dhaka Medical College Hospital. He said the food arranged for the rally's participants to mark the 'World Environmental Day' on Friday was distributed among the affected people. The national program to observe the day at Bangabandhu International Conference Centre was postponed earlier. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina was set to inaugurate the event. The country observed a national day of mourning for the fire victims on Saturday. bdnews24.com
